Post.title: Centos7redis5.0.5
Post._content:
### #### 1. 2IP192.168.1.100;192.168.1.101 (IP,;) #### 2. redis-5.0.5.tar.gz->->make->make install /usr/local/redis ### /usr/local/redis/ conf ``` bash # mkdir /usr/local/redis/conf ``` ### redis.confconfredis-6379.conf ``` bash # copy /usr/local/redis/redis.conf /usr/local/redis/conf/redis-6379.conf ``` ### redis-6379.conf ``` bash # vim /usr/local/redis/conf/redis-6379.conf ``` :
bind 127.0.0.1 bind 192.168.1.100(101192.168.1.101)
pidfile /var/run/redis_6379.pid pidfile /usr/local/redis/conf/redis_6379.pid
logfile "" logfile "/usr/local/redis/logs/redis-6379.log"
appendonly no appendonly yes
# cluster-enabled yes cluster-enabled yes
# cluster-config-file nodes-6379.conf cluster-config-file /usr/local/redis/conf/nodes-6379.conf
# cluster-node-timeout 15000 cluster-node-timeout 15000
### redis-6379.conf3,redis-6379.confredis-6380.confredis-6381.conf ``` bash # cp /usr/local/redis/conf/redis-6379.conf /usr/local/redis/conf/redis-6380.conf # cp /usr/local/redis/conf/redis-6379.conf /usr/local/redis/conf/redis-6381.conf ``` ### redis-6380.confredis-6381.conf,637963806381 ### redis,3 ``` bash # /usr/local/redis/src/redis-server /usr/local/redis/conf/redis-6379.conf & # /usr/local/redis/src/redis-server /usr/local/redis/conf/redis-6380.conf & # /usr/local/redis/src/redis-server /usr/local/redis/conf/redis-6381.conf & ``` ### redis,637963806381redis ``` bash # ps -ef | grep redis ``` ### (637963806381,163791638016381) ### redis-cli() ``` bash # /usr/local/redis/src/redis-cli --cluster create 192.168.1.100:6379 192.168.1.100:6380 192.168.1.100:6381 192.168.1.101:6379 192.168.1.101:6380 192.168.1.101:6381 --cluster-replicas 1 ``` ### type 'yes' to accept,yes,OK ### springbootpropertiesyamlspring.redis.host=xxx,yyy spring.redis.cluster.nodes=xxx,yyy

Post.title: Centos7redis5.0.5
Post._content:
,redis,~

### gcc
``` bash
# yum install gcc
```
### redis
``` bash
# wget http://download.redis.io/releases/redis-5.0.5.tar.gz
```
### 
``` bash
# tar -zxvf redis-5.0.5.tar.gz
```
### 
``` bash
# cd redis-5.0.5
# make
```
###  It's a good idea to run 'make test' . 
``` bash
# make install prefix=/usr/local/redis
```
### redis
``` bash
# /usr/local/redis/bin/redis-server
```
### redis
``` bash
# vim /usr/local/redis/redis.conf
```
####  bind 127.0.0.1 0.0.0.0
####  protected-mode  yes
####  daemonize  yes
#### . ()
### . redis5.0.5,redisutils
``` bash
# cd /usr/local/redis/utils/
# ./install_server.sh
```
#### 
###
